%N A234641 Odd numbers k such that sigma(sigma(k^2)) is odd.
%C A234641 The sum of divisors of a square is always odd, therefore these numbers have the property that x = n^2, y = sigma(x) and z = sigma(y) are all three odd.
%C A234641 This is the subsequence of odd terms of A008847.
%H A234641 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A234641/b234641.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..316</a> (terms 1..122 from M. F. Hasler)
%F A234641 a(n) = sqrt(A231484(n)). - _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 15 2026
%Y A234641 Cf. A000203, A000290, A008847, A008848, A163763, A231484.
